WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.320 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.320 --> 00:00:10.480 align:middle line:84%
Right now we have more than
7 billion people on the earth.

00:00:10.480 --> 00:00:12.730 align:middle line:10%
And our ranks are
growing quickly.

00:00:12.730 --> 00:00:14.830 align:middle line:10%
At the same time,
as automation grows,

00:00:14.830 --> 00:00:17.880 align:middle line:10%
we have less need
for so many workers.

00:00:17.880 --> 00:00:20.530 align:middle line:84%
The poet, Wendell Berry,
asked the question,

00:00:20.530 --> 00:00:22.120 align:middle line:90%
"What are people for?"

00:00:22.120 --> 00:00:24.420 align:middle line:84%
This has never seemed more
pertinent, more important

00:00:24.420 --> 00:00:26.640 align:middle line:90%
for us to answer.

00:00:26.640 --> 00:00:29.390 align:middle line:84%
Alan Watts noted that
just as the apple tree

00:00:29.390 --> 00:00:31.910 align:middle line:84%
naturally produces
fruits, as he put it,

00:00:31.910 --> 00:00:33.590 align:middle line:90%
"The apple tree apples."

00:00:33.590 --> 00:00:35.430 align:middle line:84%
The earth is
peopling, constantly

00:00:35.430 --> 00:00:37.360 align:middle line:90%
making more and more of us.

00:00:37.360 --> 00:00:40.150 align:middle line:84%
Just as apple seeds
spread to other orchards

00:00:40.150 --> 00:00:42.940 align:middle line:84%
and make more apple trees,
it might make sense,

00:00:42.940 --> 00:00:44.830 align:middle line:84%
by analogy, that the
destiny of humanity

00:00:44.830 --> 00:00:46.400 align:middle line:90%
is to settle other worlds.

00:00:46.400 --> 00:00:48.575 align:middle line:84%
In the future, I tend to
think that humanity will

00:00:48.575 --> 00:00:50.640 align:middle line:90%
aim in two directions at once.

00:00:50.640 --> 00:00:52.380 align:middle line:84%
On the one hand,
I mean, why not?

00:00:52.380 --> 00:00:55.060 align:middle line:84%
Why not build star ships
and colonize space?

00:00:55.060 --> 00:00:57.180 align:middle line:84%
On the other, why not
explore the inner dimensions

00:00:57.180 --> 00:01:00.150 align:middle line:84%
of the psycho cosmos, the realms
known to shamans and mystics

00:01:00.150 --> 00:01:01.390 align:middle line:90%
through time?

00:01:01.390 --> 00:01:03.450 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, we may learn
that the inner dimensions

00:01:03.450 --> 00:01:06.820 align:middle line:84%
within the psyche are just as
fast as the outer dimensions

00:01:06.820 --> 00:01:08.188 align:middle line:90%
of the cosmos.

00:01:08.188 --> 00:01:10.180 align:middle line:90%
