00:15:27.590 --> 00:15:30.040 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about the concept
of the technological singularity

00:15:30.040 --> 00:15:32.500 align:middle line:84%
that people like Ray
Kurzweil have been espousing.

00:15:32.500 --> 00:15:33.890 align:middle line:90%
I think it's a silly idea.

00:15:33.890 --> 00:15:36.670 align:middle line:84%
The idea is that
our technology will

00:15:36.670 --> 00:15:38.000 align:middle line:84%
reach a point where
all of a sudden

00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:39.080 align:middle line:90%
we will cease to be human.

00:15:39.080 --> 00:15:41.210 align:middle line:84%
And we'll be something
beyond human.

00:15:41.210 --> 00:15:43.010 align:middle line:84%
But Daniel, during
your lifetime and mine,

00:15:43.010 --> 00:15:46.190 align:middle line:84%
how many singularities of this
kind have we already undergone?

00:15:46.190 --> 00:15:47.390 align:middle line:84%
When you were a
little kid there was

00:15:47.390 --> 00:15:49.260 align:middle line:90%
no such thing as a cellphone.

00:15:49.260 --> 00:15:51.800 align:middle line:84%
When you were a little kid
you couldn't own a laptop.

00:15:51.800 --> 00:15:52.970 align:middle line:90%
They existed.

00:15:52.970 --> 00:15:54.400 align:middle line:90%
But you couldn't own one.

00:15:54.400 --> 00:15:57.090 align:middle line:84%
There were certainly no
such thing as an iPad.

00:15:57.090 --> 00:16:01.380 align:middle line:84%
Today-- back then, when
you walked down the street,

00:16:01.380 --> 00:16:03.690 align:middle line:84%
you could dream about
talking to people in Beijing.

00:16:03.690 --> 00:16:05.760 align:middle line:84%
But in reality, you were
bored out of your skull.

00:16:05.760 --> 00:16:07.860 align:middle line:84%
And in your brain you were
arguing with your mom.

00:16:07.860 --> 00:16:09.180 align:middle line:90%
I mean, you had nothing to do.

00:16:09.180 --> 00:16:10.920 align:middle line:90%
It was awful.

00:16:10.920 --> 00:16:13.630 align:middle line:84%
And now, you can actually
talk to a friend in Beijing

00:16:13.630 --> 00:16:14.950 align:middle line:84%
while you're walking
down the street.

00:16:14.950 --> 00:16:16.680 align:middle line:84%
People can complain
about your texting

00:16:16.680 --> 00:16:17.870 align:middle line:90%
to somebody in San Jose.

00:16:17.870 --> 00:16:18.570 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:16:18.570 --> 00:16:20.530 align:middle line:84%
On the other hand, I guess
the devil's advocate--

00:16:20.530 --> 00:16:20.710 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:16:20.710 --> 00:16:22.076 align:middle line:84%
 --a lot of people
talk about how, like,

00:16:22.076 --> 00:16:24.420 align:middle line:84%
there's sort of a
disintegration of the attention

00:16:24.420 --> 00:16:26.200 align:middle line:84%
span and inability to focus.
-There is a massive--

00:16:26.200 --> 00:16:28.400 align:middle line:84%
And there was that book
called "The Shallows,"

00:16:28.400 --> 00:16:30.440 align:middle line:84%
which looked at how the internet
has had all this negative--

00:16:30.440 --> 00:16:32.600 align:middle line:84%
It's crazy.
First of all, there are facts.

00:16:32.600 --> 00:16:35.606 align:middle line:84%
And the facts are that,
again, if you had--

00:16:35.606 --> 00:16:38.830 align:middle line:84%
if you gave the average
dumb kid-- the average kid

00:16:38.830 --> 00:16:42.265 align:middle line:84%
with an IQ of 100--
an IQ test from 1900,

00:16:42.265 --> 00:16:44.740 align:middle line:84%
a Stanford Binet
IQ Test, he would

00:16:44.740 --> 00:16:46.250 align:middle line:90%
register as a marginal genius.

00:16:46.250 --> 00:16:49.020 align:middle line:90%
100-- roughly 135 IQ.

00:16:49.020 --> 00:16:53.550 align:middle line:84%
Because the IQ points have
gone up 35 points since 1900.

00:16:53.550 --> 00:16:55.590 align:middle line:84%
And it's going up
not because we are

00:16:55.590 --> 00:16:57.160 align:middle line:90%
dumbing down in "The Shallows."

00:16:57.160 --> 00:17:00.490 align:middle line:84%
It's people like the author of
"The Shallows" who are dumb.

00:17:00.490 --> 00:17:02.610 align:middle line:84%
They're not seeing the facts
in front of their nose.

00:17:02.610 --> 00:17:04.880 align:middle line:84%
We're learning how to
integrate seven or eight

00:17:04.880 --> 00:17:08.369 align:middle line:84%
streams, perceptual streams
simultaneously, in ways

00:17:08.369 --> 00:17:09.334 align:middle line:90%
we couldn't even imagine.

