scientistic person,

00:23:21.930 --> 00:23:25.640 align:middle line:90%
and you've got a problem.

00:23:25.640 --> 00:23:28.130 align:middle line:90%
How did the cosmos come to be?

00:23:28.130 --> 00:23:31.700 align:middle line:84%
How did a nothing-- how did a
something come from a nothing?

00:23:31.700 --> 00:23:34.490 align:middle line:84%
How did that something
develop into a little ball

00:23:34.490 --> 00:23:37.270 align:middle line:84%
of space and time
expanding at super speed?

00:23:37.270 --> 00:23:38.870 align:middle line:84%
What the hell are
space and time?

00:23:38.870 --> 00:23:41.420 align:middle line:84%
Where in the world did
space and time come from?

00:23:41.420 --> 00:23:43.880 align:middle line:84%
How did the first quarks--
the first particles--

00:23:43.880 --> 00:23:47.750 align:middle line:84%
come popping out of that space
and time is if from nowhere?

00:23:47.750 --> 00:23:49.031 align:middle line:90%
How?

00:23:49.031 --> 00:23:51.560 align:middle line:90%
How did you and I get here?

00:23:51.560 --> 00:23:55.430 align:middle line:84%
These are enormous problems
of cosmic creativity.

00:23:55.430 --> 00:23:57.600 align:middle line:84%
And they haven't been
posed within science.

00:23:57.600 --> 00:24:00.000 align:middle line:84%
They are not being
posed, Daniel.

00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:02.770 align:middle line:84%
And if you don't pose a
problem you certainly are not

00:24:02.770 --> 00:24:04.060 align:middle line:90%
going to be able to solve it.

00:24:04.060 --> 00:24:08.670 align:middle line:84%
This book tries to put that
problem right in your face.

00:24:08.670 --> 00:24:11.750 align:middle line:84%
And what kind of--
what kind of ideas

00:24:11.750 --> 00:24:15.090 align:middle line:84%
do come up with as explanatory
grids or reference?

00:24:15.090 --> 00:24:17.880 align:middle line:84%
The basic idea is called
Corollary Generator Theory.

00:24:17.880 --> 00:24:20.000 align:middle line:84%
And it takes you back to
when you were in high school

00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:23.110 align:middle line:90%
and you were in geometry class.

00:24:23.110 --> 00:24:26.800 align:middle line:84%
And at the beginning of the
year they gave you four axioms.

00:24:26.800 --> 00:24:28.580 align:middle line:84%
And for the rest of
the year, every week,

00:24:28.580 --> 00:24:31.100 align:middle line:84%
you had to derive a
corollary from those axioms.

00:24:31.100 --> 00:24:34.780 align:middle line:84%
And by the end of the year you
had the whole geometric system.

00:24:34.780 --> 00:24:36.340 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:24:36.340 --> 00:24:40.440 align:middle line:84%
How was an entire geometric
system implicit in four axioms?

00:24:40.440 --> 00:24:44.780 align:middle line:10%
How was the equivalent
of an entire geometry

00:24:44.780 --> 00:24:48.780 align:middle line:10%
book implicit in
165 words of axioms?

00:24:48.780 --> 00:24:50.560 align:middle line:84%
How in the world
does that happen?

00:24:50.560 --> 00:24:54.290 align:middle line:84%
And supposing that the
universe started out like that.

00:24:54.290 --> 00:24:57.440 align:middle line:84%
Suppose the universe started out
with a handful of simple rules.

00:24:57.440 --> 00:24:58.840 align:middle line:90%
Let's say, three or four.

00:24:58.840 --> 00:25:01.390 align:middle line:84%
And then every
homework assignment,

00:25:01.390 --> 00:25:04.520 align:middle line:84%
the Universe had to derive
the next set of corollaries,

00:25:04.520 --> 00:25:06.640 align:middle line:84%
the next things implicit
in those axioms.

00:25:06.640 --> 00:25:09.070 align:middle line:84%
Have you looked at
the work of Lee Smolin?

00:25:09.070 --> 00:25:10.210 align:middle line:90%
HOWARD BLOOM: Yes, absolutely.

00:25:10.210 --> 00:25:12.240 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he had an idea,
a cosmological idea,

00:25:12.240 --> 00:25:14.180 align:middle line:84%
