00:39:30.003 --> 00:39:30.890 align:middle line:90%
MIKI AGRAWAL: Yeah, OK.

00:39:30.890 --> 00:39:32.854 align:middle line:90%
So Hi, Amber, how are you?

00:39:32.854 --> 00:39:33.554 align:middle line:90%
Hi.

00:39:33.554 --> 00:39:34.390 align:middle line:90%
Hi, Howard.

00:39:34.390 --> 00:39:36.970 align:middle line:84%
So I guess my-- I went
to Cornell University.

00:39:36.970 --> 00:39:39.740 align:middle line:84%
And my journey began like
a typical college graduate,

00:39:39.740 --> 00:39:41.200 align:middle line:90%
working in investment banking.

00:39:41.200 --> 00:39:43.030 align:middle line:90%
And then 9/11 happened.

00:39:43.030 --> 00:39:45.440 align:middle line:10%
And I was supposed to
be there on that day,

00:39:45.440 --> 00:39:46.260 align:middle line:10%
working on Wall Street.

00:39:46.260 --> 00:39:48.710 align:middle line:84%
But that day I happened to
sleep through my alarm clock.

00:39:48.710 --> 00:39:50.300 align:middle line:84%
And I was just
supposed to be there.

00:39:50.300 --> 00:39:51.270 align:middle line:90%
Two people in my office died.

00:39:51.270 --> 00:39:53.100 align:middle line:84%
It was one of those
crazy experiences.

00:39:53.100 --> 00:39:56.687 align:middle line:84%
And I just started asking
myself questions after that.

00:39:56.687 --> 00:39:58.120 align:middle line:84%
Like, you know, what
am I passionate about?

00:39:58.120 --> 00:40:00.040 align:middle line:84%
What am I here--
what's my purpose?

00:40:00.040 --> 00:40:01.740 align:middle line:84%
And that's I started
writing things down.

00:40:01.740 --> 00:40:03.420 align:middle line:84%
And I kind of wrote
down three things.

00:40:03.420 --> 00:40:05.490 align:middle line:84%
One was to play
soccer professionally.

00:40:05.490 --> 00:40:06.870 align:middle line:90%
One was to make movies.

00:40:06.870 --> 00:40:08.970 align:middle line:84%
And the other was
to start a business.

00:40:08.970 --> 00:40:11.380 align:middle line:90%
And so I just, I did all three.

00:40:11.380 --> 00:40:14.160 align:middle line:10%
I played soccer for
the New York Magic

00:40:14.160 --> 00:40:16.160 align:middle line:10%
and then hurt my--
and blew out my knees.

00:40:16.160 --> 00:40:17.280 align:middle line:90%
The story's in the book.

00:40:17.280 --> 00:40:19.680 align:middle line:84%
And then I worked in
the film business.

00:40:19.680 --> 00:40:21.824 align:middle line:84%
And I worked my
way up from a PA,

00:40:21.824 --> 00:40:23.090 align:middle line:84%
like, picking up
trash in the streets.

00:40:23.090 --> 00:40:25.501 align:middle line:84%
My Asian parents were like, what
are you doing out of Cornell?

00:40:25.501 --> 00:40:26.900 align:middle line:84%
You know, picking up
trash in the streets?

00:40:26.900 --> 00:40:30.180 align:middle line:84%
But worked my way up pretty
quickly and into producing

00:40:30.180 --> 00:40:31.474 align:middle line:90%
commercials and music videos.

00:40:31.474 --> 00:40:33.340 align:middle line:84%
And that's when my stomach
started hurting all the time.

00:40:33.340 --> 00:40:34.673 align:middle line:84%
And that's when my
sort of Eureka moment

00:40:34.673 --> 00:40:37.760 align:middle line:84%
began for my first
business, which was

00:40:37.760 --> 00:40:39.440 align:middle line:90%
an alternative pizza concept.

00:40:39.440 --> 00:40:41.430 align:middle line:84%
So I had sort of
started, you know,

00:40:41.430 --> 00:40:43.470 align:middle line:84%
getting stomach aches
every time I came home.

00:40:43.470 --> 00:40:45.410 align:middle line:84%
And I was like, what
is going on my stomach?

00:40:45.410 --> 00:40:46.480 align:middle line:90%
And I started researching.

00:40:46.480 --> 00:40:48.900 align:middle line:84%
And I discovered that I
was lactose intolerant.

00:40:48.900 --> 00:40:50.510 align:middle line:84%
And I just stopped
eating dairy to see.

00:40:50.510 --> 00:40:51.290 align:middle line:90%
And it actually worked.

00:40:51.290 --> 00:40:55.170 align:middle line:84%
My bloating and my gas and
all that stuff, went away.

00:40:55.170 --> 00:40:58.270 align:middle line:84%
And I-- and I just-- but
then I went to Europe.

00:40:58.270 --> 00:41:00.830 align:middle line:84%
And I went to, like, this,
you know, French countryside.

00:41:00.830 --> 00:41:03.450 align:middle line:84%
And I ate tons of cheese because
that's what you do in Europe.

00:41:03.450 --> 00:41:04.395 align:middle line:90%
And nothing happened.

00:41:04.395 --> 00:41:07.420 align:middle line:84%
So I started asking myself,
like, why am I not-- why-- why,

00:41:07.420 --> 00:41:09.230 align:middle line:84%
when I go to Europe,
and to a French

00:41:09.230 --> 00:41:12.130 align:middle line:84%
countryside I can eat dairy, but
when I come to the US I can't?

00:41:12.130 --> 00:41:13.230 align:middle line:84%
And in more research
I discovered

00:41:13.230 --> 00:41:16.890 align:middle line:84%
that it's the process-- it's the
way dairy is being processed.

00:41:16.890 --> 00:41:19.070 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, so all this to
say, I had I'd given

00:41:19.070 --> 00:41:21.000 align:middle line:90%
up pizza at the time in the US.

00:41:21.000 --> 00:41:23.505 align:middle line:84%
And I researched pizza
and discovered that

00:41:23.505 --> 00:41:25.100 align:middle line:90%
it's a $32-billion industry.

00:41:25.100 --> 00:41:27.400 align:middle line:84%
Americans eat 100 acres
of pizza every day.

00:41:27.400 --> 00:41:28.500 align:middle line:90%
And you know?

00:41:28.500 --> 00:41:31.913 align:middle line:84%
And why were they not making
pizza for those-- you know,

00:41:31.913 --> 00:41:32.890 align:middle line:90%
who had intolerances?

00:41:32.890 --> 00:41:34.490 align:middle line:84%
You know, right
now, there are 20%

00:41:34.490 --> 00:41:37.030 align:middle line:90%
of Americans eat gluten free.

00:41:37.030 --> 00:41:39.060 align:middle line:84%
You know, one in five Americans
are lactose intolerant.

00:41:39.060 --> 00:41:40.390 align:middle line:84%
They're just these
huge statistics.

00:41:40.390 --> 00:41:43.610 align:middle line:84%
And the big giant pizza
industry leaders weren't

00:41:43.610 --> 00:41:44.470 align:middle line:90%
making it better for you.

00:41:44.470 --> 00:41:45.207 align:middle line:90%
As I said, screw it.

00:41:45.207 --> 00:41:46.240 align:middle line:90%
I've no experience in anything.

00:41:46.240 --> 00:41:47.639 align:middle line:84%
But I'm just going to
start a pizza place.

00:41:47.639 --> 00:41:49.990 align:middle line:84%
And so I started my
first farm-to-table pizza

00:41:49.990 --> 00:41:52.080 align:middle line:90%
place called Slice.

00:41:52.080 --> 00:41:53.415 align:middle line:90%
And now it's called Wild.

00:41:53.415 --> 00:41:54.660 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

